'''Moutaz Neffati''' ({{langx|ar|معتز نفّاتي}}; born 4 September 2004) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right-back]] for the [[Allsvenskan]] club [[IFK Norrköping]]. Born in Sweden, he plays for the [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia national team]].

==Club career==
A youth product of {{ill|Hageby IF|sv}}, Neffati finished his development with [[IFK Norrköping|Norrköping]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nt.se/sport/fotboll/artikel/ifks-17-arige-a-lagsdebutant-det-var-nervost/r19vv71j|title=IFK:s 17-årige A-lagsdebutant: "Det var nervöst"|first=David|last=Iwung|date=14 February 2022|website=www.nt.se|language=sv}}</ref> On 10 June 2022, he signed his first professional contract with Norrköping for the 2023 season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fotbolltransfers.com/nyheter/officiellt-ifk-norrkoping-skriver-kontrakt-med-moutaz-neffati/154334|title=Officiellt: IFK Norrköping skriver kontrakt med Moutaz Neffati|website=fotbolltransfers.com|language=sv}}</ref> He went on loan with [[IF Sylvia|Sylvia]] in the [[Ettan Fotboll|Ettan]] tournament.<ref name="auto">{{Cite web|url=https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/bloggar/sillybloggen/2024/04/25/officiellt-norrkoping-lanar-ut-neffati-till-reykjavik/|title=Officiellt: Norrköping lånar ut Neffati till Reykjavik|website=fotbollskanalen}}</ref> He returned to Norrköping and on 17 November 2023 signed a professional contract with the club for 3 seasons.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ifknorrkoping.se/moutaz-neffati-skriver-a-lagskontrakt/|title=Moutaz Neffati skriver A-lagskontrakt|first=Erik|last=Johansson|date=17 November 2023|language=sv}}</ref> On 25 April 2024, he joined the Icelandic club [[Knattspyrnufélag Reykjavíkur|KR]] on loan for 2 months.<ref name="auto"/> He returned to [[IFK Norrköping|Norrköping]] in 2024, where he was integrated with the first team. On 13 September 2025, he extended his contract with Norrköping until 2028.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fotbolltransfers.com/nyheter/officiellt-moutaz-neffati-forlanger-med-ifk-norrkoping/200077|title=Officiellt: Moutaz Neffati förlänger med IFK Norrköping|website=fotbolltransfers.com|language=sv}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in Sweden, Neffati is of Tunisian descent and holds dual Swedish-Tunisian citizenship.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ca.sports.yahoo.com/news/moutaz-neffati-chooses-tunisia-091500294.html|title=Moutaz Neffati chooses Tunisia|date=11 August 2025|website=Yahoo Sports}}</ref> In March 2025, he debuted for the [[Sweden men's national under-21 football team|Sweden U21]]s.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ifknorrkoping.se/neffe-om-landslagschansen-en-klapp-pa-axeln/|title="Neffe" om landslagschansen: "En klapp på axeln"|first=David|last=Iwung|date=13 March 2025}}</ref> In August 2025, he opted to play for the [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia national team]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportnewsafrica.com/breve/moutaz-neffati-zappe-la-suede-et-choisit-la-tunisie/|title=Moutaz Neffati zappe la Suède et choisit la Tunisie|first=John|last=Attisso|language=fr|archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20250813142748/https://sportnewsafrica.com/breve/moutaz-neffati-zappe-la-suede-et-choisit-la-tunisie/|archive-date=2025-08-13}}</ref> He made his debut for Tunisia in October 2025.

